# Euler Problem: Computing GC Content in Scala

## Problem Statement
The GC content of a DNA string is the percentage of symbols in the string that are 'G' or 'C'. Given at most 10 DNA strings in FASTA format (of length at most 1000 nucleotides), return the ID of the string having the highest GC content, followed by the GC content of that string.

## Solution Approach
1. Parse FASTA format input to extract DNA sequences
2. Calculate GC content for each sequence
3. Find the sequence with maximum GC content
4. Output the result in required format

## Scala Implementation

```scala
import scala.io.Source
import scala.collection.mutable

object GCContent {
  def main(args: Array[String]): Unit = {
    // Read input from file or stdin
    val input = Source.fromFile("rosalind_gc.txt").getLines().toList
    
    val sequences = parseFASTA(input)
    val maxGC = findMaxGC(sequences)
    
    println(s"${maxGC._1}")
    println(f"${maxGC._2 * 100}%.6f")
  }
  
  def parseFASTA(lines: List[String]): Map[String, String] = {
    val sequences = mutable.Map[String, String]()
    var currentId = ""
    var currentSeq = new StringBuilder
    
    lines.foreach { line =>
      if (line.startsWith(">")) {
        if (currentId.nonEmpty) {
          sequences(currentId) = currentSeq.toString
        }
        currentId = line.substring(1)
        currentSeq.clear()
      } else {
        currentSeq.append(line)
      }
    }
    
    // Don't forget the last sequence
    if (currentId.nonEmpty) {
      sequences(currentId) = currentSeq.toString
    }
    
    sequences.toMap
  }
  
  def calculateGCContent(dna: String): Double = {
    val gcCount = dna.count(c => c == 'G' || c == 'C')
    val totalCount = dna.length
    if (totalCount == 0) 0.0 else gcCount.toDouble / totalCount
  }
  
  def findMaxGC(sequences: Map[String, String]): (String, Double) = {
    sequences.maxBy { case (_, dna) => calculateGCContent(dna) }
  }
}
```
